
@startuml
' Define classes and their attributes

class School {
  -name: String
}

class Teacher {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
}

class Student {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
}

class Principal {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
}

class Room {
  -name: String
}

class Classroom extends Room {
  -capacity: Integer
}

class Gym extends Room {
  -size: Integer
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
}

' Define associations and multiplicities

School "1" *-- "0..*" Teacher : employs
School "1" *-- "1" Principal : hasPrincipal
Teacher "0..3" *-- "1" School : teachesAt
Teacher "0..1" *-- "1" School : isPrincipalOf

School "1" *-- "0..*" Room : hasRoom

Student "1" *-- "1" School : attends
Student "1" *-- "1" ClassGroup : belongsTo
ClassGroup "1" *-- "1" Classroom : assignedTo
ClassGroup "1" *-- "10..31" Student : contains

' Inheritance
Teacher <|-- Principal
Room <|-- Classroom
Room <|-- Gym

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:

- **School**:
  - Has many `Teachers` (via employment).
  - Has exactly one `Principal`, who must be a `Teacher`.
  - Has many `Rooms`.

- **Teacher**:
  - Can teach at up to three `Schools`.
  - Can be the principal of only one `School`.

- **Student**:
  - Attends exactly one `School`.
  - Belongs to exactly one `ClassGroup`.

- **ClassGroup**:
  - Contains between 10 and 31 `Students`.
  - Assigned to exactly one `Classroom`.

- **Room**:
  - Base class for both `Classroom` and `Gym`.
  - `Classroom` has a `capacity`, `Gym` has a `size`.

